  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To maintain a professional work environment free from conflicts of interest and the appearance of impropriety by addressing the hiring of relatives and the management of personal relationships within the workplace.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefinition of \u0022Relative\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E For this policy, \u0022relative\u0022 includes, but is not limited to, spouse, domestic partner, parent, child, sibling, grandparent, grandchild, aunt, uncle, niece, nephew, and corresponding in-laws.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHiring of Relatives:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo Direct Reporting:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Generally prohibits employment where one relative would directly supervise, manage, or otherwise have control over the work, performance, or terms and conditions of employment of the other (e.g., hiring, firing, promotion, salary adjustments, disciplinary action).\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAvoidance of Conflict:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Even in non-reporting relationships, if the employment of relatives could create a perceived or actual conflict of interest, preferential treatment, or an adverse impact on morale, such employment may be avoided.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisclosure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Applicants and employees must disclose any existing or potential familial relationships with current Neumo employees during the application process or as they arise during employment. Failure to disclose such relationships may result in disciplinary action.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPersonal Relationships (Non-Relative)\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo Direct Reporting:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Employees in a romantic or close personal relationship that develops during employment are prohibited from being in a direct reporting relationship where one has supervisory authority over the other. If such a relationship develops, one employee must notify the People \u0026amp; Culture Team, and the Company will work to find an appropriate transfer or other resolution.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProfessional Conduct:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Regardless of any personal relationship, all employees must maintain professional conduct in the workplace and adhere to all company policies, including those on harassment and workplace conduct. Personal displays of affection in the workplace are generally inappropriate.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConflict of Interest:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Relationships must not create actual/perceived conflicts of interest or otherwise interfere with business operations, objectivity, or fairness in employment decisions.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsequences of Violation\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Failure to comply (including non-disclosure or creating prohibited relationships/conflicts) may result in disciplinary action (reassignment, demotion, or termination).\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E"
}]]></Value>
    </fullPolicyText>
